<TITLE> Minibus torched as one killed in Mirpur road crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 18 (bdnews24.com)  People went berserk in the city's Mirpur on Friday morning following death of a young man in a road crash and torched a minibus, police said. After a minibus knocked down Abdul Karim, 30, under Shewrhaparha foot overbridge at around 7:30am, infuriated local people stopped the bus, manhandled its driver and set fire to the vehicle, witnesses and police said. Traffic movement on Rokeya Sharani remained suspended for an hour following the accident. Syed Jamiul Islam, police constable on duty at the scene, told bdnews24.com, "Karim was crossing the road under the overbridge when a Sadarghat-bound minibus of United Poribahan knocked him down. He was killed on the spot." Kafrul police chief Delwar Ahmed said that the victim, Karim hailed from Atwari upazila of Panchagarh district and was employed as peon at a local readymade garments factory. Eye witnesses said angry mob torched the bus immediately after the accident and beat the bus driver severely, leaving him critically wounded on the road. Police said the critically injured and unidentified bus driver was sent to Dhaka Medical College Hospital. Traffic mobility on the road was restored at around 8:30am, he said. bdnew
